  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is a list of formula sheets for each subject for the GATE in mechanical to cope with last minute preparation?",
  "response": "For last-minute preparation for the GATE (Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering) in Mechanical Engineering, having a concise list of formula sheets can be incredibly useful. Here's a list of formula sheets for each major subject area in Mechanical Engineering:\n\n1. **Engineering Mathematics**\n   - Linear Algebra: Matrix operations, eigenvalues, eigenvectors.\n   - Calculus: Limits, continuity, differentiation, integration, differential equations.\n   - Probability and Statistics: Probability distributions, mean, median, mode, standard deviation.\n   - Complex Numbers: Functions, polar form, Euler's formula.\n   - Numerical Methods: Newton-Raphson method, interpolation formulas, numerical integration.\n\n2. **Engineering Mechanics**\n   - Statics: Free body diagrams, equilibrium equations.\n   - Dynamics: Kinematics, Newton's laws of motion, energy methods.\n   - Strength of Materials: Stress-strain relations, bending moment diagrams, shear force, torsion.\n\n3. **Fluid Mechanics**\n   - Properties of Fluids: Density, viscosity, surface tension.\n   - Fluid Statics: Pressure variation, buoyancy.\n   - Fluid Dynamics: Bernoulli's equation, continuity equation, Reynolds number, boundary layers.\n\n4. **Thermodynamics**\n   - Laws of Thermodynamics: Zeroth, first, second, and third laws.\n   - Thermodynamic Processes: Isothermal, adiabatic, isobaric, isochoric.\n   - Thermodynamic Cycles: Carnot cycle, Rankine cycle, Brayton cycle.\n\n5. **Heat Transfer**\n   - Conduction: Fourier's law, thermal resistance.\n   - Convection: Newton's law of cooling, Nusselt number.\n   - Radiation: Stefan-Boltzmann law, emissivity.\n\n6. **Manufacturing Engineering**\n   - Metal Casting: Solidification, gating system design.\n   - Forming: Stress and strain in rolling, forging, extrusion.\n   - Joining: Welding processes, soldering, brazing.\n   - Machining: Cutting forces, tool life, machining time calculations.\n\n7. **Machine Design**\n   - Design of Machine Elements: Bolts, rivets, welded joints, shafts, gears.\n   - Failure theories: Maximum stress, maximum strain energy, Mohr's circle.\n\n8. **Theory of Machines**\n   - Kinematics of Machines: Velocity and acceleration diagrams.\n   - Mechanisms: Four-bar linkages, cam profiles.\n   - Dynamics of Machines: Balancing, flywheels, governors.\n\n9. **Industrial Engineering**\n   - Work Study: Time and motion study.\n   - Production Planning and Control: Inventory models, scheduling.\n   - Quality Control: Control charts, acceptance sampling.\n\n10. **Vibrations**\n   - Free and Forced Vibrations: Natural frequency, damping.\n   - Vibration Isolation: Vibration absorbers.\n\n11. **Material Science**\n   - Crystal structure: FCC, BCC, HCP.\n   - Phase Diagrams: Iron-carbon diagram.\n   - Mechanical Properties: Hardness, toughness, ductility.\n\nHaving these formulas and basic principles at your fingertips can significantly accelerate your review process and ensure you're ready for the exam. Good luck!",
